FRANCE DAYBOOK: G20 Investment Summit; Consumer Confidence

-- B y  
-- 
2011-06-24T04:10:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/france-daybook-g20-investment-summit-consumer-confidence.html
The G20 Investment Summit of
company executives meets in Paris.  ALL TIMES CET  WHAT TO WATCH:
* G20 Investment Summit conference, Intercontinental Hotel  EARNINGS * No major earnings scheduled  ECONOMY: Data and events today
* 8:45 a.m. Consumer Confidence (June)  GOVERNMENT:
* OECD Sec-Gen Angel Gurria press conference 10:00 a.m.
* President Sarkozy press conference in Brussels 2:45 p.m.
* Foreign Trade Minister Lellouche speaks on competitiveness
4:00 p.m.  EQUITIES:
* Total SA (FP FP):  France ’s Industry Minister Eric Besson
asked Total SA to modify gasoline prices for consumers after
the  International Energy Agency  said its members would release
crude from strategic reserves. The shares fell 1.6 percent to
37.97 euros.  *Areva SA (AREVA FP): The world’s largest builder of nuclear
reactors and the China Nuclear Power Technology Research
Institute created a joint venture BRIC specializing in the
construction and maintenance of reactor incore I&C for Chinese
COR-1000 power plants, the company said in an e-mailed
statement today. The shares added 2.6 percent to 26.01 euros.  * Netgem SA (NTG FP): The supplier of set-top television boxes
said Virgin Mobile France selected it to provide technology for
its Virgin Box TV. The shares dropped 2.5 percent to 3.50
euros.  * Sanofi-Aventis (SAN FP): France’s largest drugmaker received
market authorization in  Canada  for Jevtana. The shares dropped
1 percent to 52.29 euros.  * Vinci SA (DG FP): Europe’s largest construction group signed
a five-year revolving credit facility for 4 billion euros with
a group of 23 banks, the company said in an e-mailed statement
today. The shares fell 1.9 percent to 41.72 euros.  MARKETS:
*The CAC 40 Index fell 83.58 points, or 2.2 percent, to
3,787.79 in Paris.
*The broader SBF 120 Index declined 2.1 percent to 2,860.89
points.  INTERVIEWS ELSEWHERE:
-07:40 Canal Plus: Ecology Minister Nathalie Kosciusko-Morizet
-07:50 France 2: Health Minister Xavier Bertrand
-07:50 RTL: Bank of France Governor Christian Noyer
-08:13 i-Tele: Agriculture Minister Bruno Le Maire
-08:15 LCI: Debout la Republique’s Nicolas Dupont-Aignan
-08:15 France Info: Sports Minister Chantal Jouanno
-08:20  Europe  1: AMF President Jean-Pierre Jouyet
-08:35 RMC: Christian Democrat Christine Boutin
-10:20 BFM Radio: Archos CEO Henri Crohas
